elements.title: Antonette Wemyss Gorman
elements.contents: ... that Antonette Wemyss Gorman (pictured), the first woman to fill a combat role in the Caribbean, was promoted to rear admiral and is Chief of Defence Staff of the Jamaica Defence Force?

elements.title: Matilda Allison
elements.contents: ... that Matilda Allison, blinded aged seven, "devoted her time instructing the blind" throughout America, thanks to a "wonderful education"?

elements.title: Shirley McGreal
elements.contents: ... that British animal-welfare activist Shirley McGreal founded the International Primate Protection League, after seeing trafficked monkeys in cages at an airport in Thailand?

elements.title: Janine Brookner
elements.contents: ... that three former top-ranking Central Intelligence Agency officials appeared on ABC News Nightline to condemn the agency's treatment of Janine Brookner?

elements.title: Dorthe Emilie Røssell
elements.contents: ... that, between the ages of six and ten, Dorthe Emilie Røssell helped smuggle weapons and propaganda for the Danish resistance movement in her doll's pram?

elements.title: Julie Croteau
elements.contents: ... that Julie Croteau is credited as being the first woman to play National Collegiate Athletic Association men's college baseball?

elements.title: Stella Madzimbamuto
elements.contents: ... that South African nurse Stella Madzimbamuto filed an appeal in 1968 with the Privy Council of the United Kingdom that resulted in the Rhodesian government being declared illegal?

elements.title: Margaret Lemon
elements.contents: ... that the popular artist's model Margaret Lemon tried to bite Anthony van Dyck's thumb off?
